@aaronfranklin324 ... yep tar and bitumen are flammable.
Of course I was mainly joking, but it is a valid thing to think about. Hot coals fall out the bottom then wind can blow them around anywhere.
A good fire/stove design contains the coals safely within, and has some system to rake out the dead coals later for disposal.

@ThinkingandTinkering I know the rocket stove burns much cleaner and more efficient.  But it still must get some particles in the air. Unless it use some kind of filter. Even a candle gives some unhealty  particles to the room. I know you can't compare candle with wood. 
This wasn't an attack on you. I hvave never used rocket stove. So it is just a theory from my side. 
So you saying that a rocket stove do not give any kind of particles or smell to the room, if you burn it indoors?
